infn.bed.event

Class ChargeTimeData

  • java.lang.Object
    • infn.bed.event.ChargeTimeData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILoad

    public class ChargeTimeData
extends java.lang.Object
implements ILoad
    This class handles the reading in of a charge-time data file. It also converts the full waveform data to charge-time data in a special constructor. This allows the view classes to base their code off this class.
    Author:
    Andy Beiter

      • load

        public void load(org.jlab.coda.jevio.IEvioStructure structure,
        int tag,
        int num)
        Loads in the charge-time data from a charge-time file. Tag 102 is for bars and tag 202 is for vetoes. Numbers 1-7 gets the sector, layer/intOrExt, paddle/channel, chargeLeft/1, chargeRight/2, timeLeft/1, and timeRight/2 arrays, respectively.
        Specified by:
        load in interface ILoad
        Parameters:
        structure - The data
        tag - The tag used to identify the data
        num - The number used to identify the data
